fields.bio: This is a user which is useful for testing, but should be deleted on any live website. The password is predefined and comitted to a repository and so as a public password is not in any way secure. This user has access to everything and is generally considered 'root' for this website. And this is why it is not a good idea to keep this user. Instead each person who wishes to be an administrator of a live or staging web site should have their own accounts and then be added to the right groups with the required permissions.
